description: Number of partitions of n into parts of 7 kinds.
comments: a(n) is Euler transform of A010727. - _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
links: Vincenzo Librandi, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..200
Index entries for expansions of Product_{k >= 1} (1-x^k)^m
formula: G.f.: Product_{m>=1} 1/(1-x^m)^7.a(n) ~ 49 * exp(Pi * sqrt(14*n/3)) / (576 * sqrt(2) * n^(5/2)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 28 2015
maple: with(numtheory): a:= proc(n) option remember; `if`(n=0, 1, add(add(d*7, d=divisors(j)) *a(n-j), j=1..n)/n) end: seq(a(n), n=0..40); # _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
crossrefs: Cf. 7th column of A144064. - _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
